messages.original: The 7 Tu-95MS from Olenya Airbase are approaching the launch lines in Mokshansky District, Penza Oblast. They will likely carry out simulated launch maneuvers from there and continue flying to Engels District, Saratov Oblast.
10 Kalibrs have entered Ukrainian airspace. Map soon
3 groups of Kalibrs entered Kherson Oblast via Nova Kakhova and are flying northwest to Bashtanka, Mykolaiv Oblast.

1 Kalibr flew to Zaporizhzhia City and impacted.
3 groups of Kalibrs continue flying northwest through Mykolaiv Oblast.
2 Kalibrs are flying to Kherson.
Another explosion in Zaporizhzhia. Kalibrs again.

2 groups of Kalibrs flew past Kherson towards Mykolaiv. 
3 groups of Kalibrs are flying northwest towards Vozsiyats'ke, Mykolaiv Oblast.
2 Kalibrs (1 group) impacted Zaporizhzhia.
They seem to be flying in pairs.

2 pairs of Kalibrs flew past Mykolaiv to Nova Odesa, Mykolaiv Oblast.
3 pairs of Kalibrs entered Kirovohrad Oblast, flying northwest to Uman, Cherkasy Oblast. The pairs are flying one after another.

Sudanese Government Says 2,000 Civilians Were Killed By Rapid Support Forces In El-Fasher (18+ Videos)
Thousands of Sudanese civilians have been reportedly killed by the Rapid Support Forces (RSF) in el-Fashe after the withdrawal of the Sudanese Armed Forces (SAF) from the city in western Sudan.
Horrific videos purported to show RSF militants rounding up and executing civilians near el-Fasher began to surface online right after the fall of the city on October 26.
During a press conference in the city of Port Sudan on October 29, Mona Nour Al-Daem, Sudan's Deputy Commissioner of Humanitarian Aid, said that at least 2,000 civilians were killed by the RSF in el-Fasher, describing what happened as "genocide against unarmed civilians."
